(1) Ocean Ave., at the S.E. corner of Voorhies Ave., showing the Sheephead Bay M.E. Church, erected in 1840. John Y. Mc Kane a member of this church and Superintendent of the Sunday School for over 20 years was born in Ireland in 1841 and settled in Gravesend in 1842, where he married the daughter of Capt. Cornelius B. Nostrand in 1865. The building in this view was erected in 1869.

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, at a later date.

August 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

A view of Memorial Hall and Bill Brown Post of the American Legion, named in honor of the first American to fall in battle. (Former Comptroller Cunningham was a member of this Post.)
